<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Purpose </inglise>
<eesti> Eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of this Directive is to lay down a general framework for combating discrimination on the grounds of religion or belief, disability, age or sexual orientation as regards employment and occupation, with a view to putting into effect in the Member States the principle of equal treatment. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on kehtestada &uuml;ldine raamistik, et v&otilde;idelda usutunnistuse v&otilde;i veendumuste, puude, vanuse v&otilde;i seksuaalse s&auml;ttumuse alusel diskrimineerimise vastu t&ouml;&ouml; saamisel ja kutsealale p&auml;&auml;semisel ning tagada liikmesriikides v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte rakendamine. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Concept of discrimination </inglise>
<eesti> Diskrimineerimise m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive, the "principle of equal treatment" shall mean that there shall be no direct or indirect discrimination whatsoever on any of the grounds referred to in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel t&auml;hendab "v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;te", et ei esine otsest ega kaudset diskrimineerimist &uuml;helgi artiklis 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of paragraph 1: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 kohaldamisel: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) direct discrimination shall be taken to occur where one person is treated less favourably than another is, has been or would be treated in a comparable situation, on any of the grounds referred to in Article 1; </inglise>
<eesti> a) peetakse otseseks diskrimineerimiseks seda, kui &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millisel artiklis 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjusel koheldakse &uuml;hte inimest halvemini, kui on koheldud, koheldakse v&otilde;i v&otilde;idakse kohelda teist inimest samalaadses olukorras; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) indirect discrimination shall be taken to occur where an apparently neutral provision, criterion or practice would put persons having a particular religion or belief, a particular disability, a particular age, or a particular sexual orientation at a particular disadvantage compared with other persons unless: </inglise>
<eesti> b) peetakse kaudseks diskrimineerimiseks seda, kui v&auml;liselt neutraalne s&auml;te, kriteerium v&otilde;i tava seab konkreetse usutunnistuse v&otilde;i veendumuste, puude, vanuse v&otilde;i seksuaalse s&auml;ttumusega isikud teistega v&otilde;rreldes ebasoodsamasse olukorda, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) that provision, criterion or practice is objectively justified by a legitimate aim and the means of achieving that aim are appropriate and necessary, or </inglise>
<eesti> i) k&otilde;nealusel s&auml;ttel, kriteeriumil v&otilde;i taval on objektiivselt p&otilde;hjendatav &otilde;igustatud eesm&auml;rk ja selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamise vahendid on asjakohased ja vajalikud v&otilde;i kui </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) as regards persons with a particular disability, the employer or any person or organisation to whom this Directive applies, is obliged, under national legislation, to take appropriate measures in line with the principles contained in Article 5 in order to eliminate disadvantages entailed by such provision, criterion or practice. </inglise>
<eesti> ii) teatava puudega inimeste puhul t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i iga isik v&otilde;i organisatsioon, kelle suhtes k&auml;esolev direktiiv kehtib, on vastavalt siseriiklikele &otilde;igusaktidele kohustatud v&otilde;tma artiklis 5 sisalduvate p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega koosk&otilde;las olevaid asjakohaseid meetmeid, et k&otilde;rvaldada sellisest s&auml;ttest, kriteeriumist v&otilde;i tavast tulenevat halvemust. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Harassment shall be deemed to be a form of discrimination within the meaning of paragraph 1, when unwanted conduct related to any of the grounds referred to in Article 1 takes place with the purpose or effect of violating the dignity of a person and of creating an intimidating, hostile, degrading, humiliating or offensive environment. </inglise>
