<inglise> Notwithstanding Article 2(1) and (2), Member States may provide that a difference of treatment which is based on a characteristic related to any of the grounds referred to in Article 1 shall not constitute discrimination where, by reason of the nature of the particular occupational activities concerned or of the context in which they are carried out, such a characteristic constitutes a genuine and determining occupational requirement, provided that the objective is legitimate and the requirement is proportionate. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata artikli 2 l&otilde;igetest 1 ja 2, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid ette n&auml;ha, et erinevat kohtlemist &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millise artiklis 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjusega seotud omaduse alusel ei peeta diskrimineerimiseks, kui see omadus on teatud kutsetegevuse laadi v&otilde;i sellega liituvate tingimuste t&otilde;ttu oluline ja m&auml;&auml;rav kutsen&otilde;ue, tingimusel, et eesm&auml;rk on &otilde;igustatud ja n&otilde;ue sellega proportsionaalne. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may maintain national legislation in force at the date of adoption of this Directive or provide for future legislation incorporating national practices existing at the date of adoption of this Directive pursuant to which, in the case of occupational activities within churches and other public or private organisations the ethos of which is based on religion or belief, a difference of treatment based on a person's religion or belief shall not constitute discrimination where, by reason of the nature of these activities or of the context in which they are carried out, a person's religion or belief constitute a genuine, legitimate and justified occupational requirement, having regard to the organisation's ethos. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad s&auml;ilitada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;eval j&otilde;us olevad siseriiklikud &otilde;igusaktid v&otilde;i kehtestada uusi &otilde;igusakte, mis sisaldavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;eval kehtivaid siseriiklikke tavasid, mille kohaselt kutsetegevuse puhul kirikutes ja teistes usutunnistusel v&otilde;i veendumustel p&otilde;hineva eetosega avalikes v&otilde;i eraorganisatsioonides ei peeta isiku erinevat kohtlemist tema diskrimineerimiseks usutunnistuse v&otilde;i veendumuste alusel, kui isiku usutunnistus v&otilde;i veendumus on nimetatud tegevuse laadi v&otilde;i sellega liituvate tingimuste t&otilde;ttu oluline &otilde;igustatav ja p&otilde;hjendatud, organisatsiooni eetost silmas pidav kutsen&otilde;ue. </eesti>
<inglise> This difference of treatment shall be implemented taking account of Member States' constitutional provisions and principles, as well as the general principles of Community law, and should not justify discrimination on another ground. </inglise>
<eesti> Erineva kohtlemise rakendamisel v&otilde;etakse arvesse liikmesriigi p&otilde;hiseaduse s&auml;tteid ja p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid ning &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse &uuml;ldisi p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid ning sellega ei tohiks &otilde;igustada diskrimineerimist mingil muul alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Provided that its provisions are otherwise complied with, this Directive shall thus not prejudice the right of churches and other public or private organisations, the ethos of which is based on religion or belief, acting in conformity with national constitutions and laws, to require individuals working for them to act in good faith and with loyalty to the organisation's ethos. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&auml;esoleva direktiivi muid s&auml;tteid j&auml;rgitakse, ei piira see kirikute ja teiste usutunnistusel v&otilde;i veendumustel p&otilde;hineva eetosega ning vastavalt riigi p&otilde;hiseadusele ja &otilde;igusaktidele toimivate avalike v&otilde;i eraorganisatsioonide &otilde;igust n&otilde;uda nende heaks t&ouml;&ouml;tavatelt isikutelt tegutsemist heas usus ning lojaalsust organisatsiooni eetosele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Reasonable accommodation for disabled persons </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;istlikud abin&otilde;ud puuetega inimeste arvessev&otilde;tmiseks </eesti>
<inglise> In order to guarantee compliance with the principle of equal treatment in relation to persons with disabilities, reasonable accommodation shall be provided. </inglise>
<eesti> Et tagada puuetega inimeste v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgimine, n&auml;hakse ette m&otilde;istlikud abin&otilde;ud. </eesti>
<inglise> This means that employers shall take appropriate measures, where needed in a particular case, to enable a person with a disability to have access to, participate in, or advance in employment, or to undergo training, unless such measures would impose a disproportionate burden on the employer. </inglise>
<eesti> See t&auml;hendab seda, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjad v&otilde;tavad asjakohaseid, konkreetsel juhul vajalikke meetmeid, et v&otilde;imaldada puuetega inimesel t&ouml;&ouml;le p&auml;&auml;seda, t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda v&otilde;i edeneda v&otilde;i saada koolitust, kui sellised meetmed ei p&otilde;hjusta t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ebaproportsionaalselt suurt koormust. </eesti>
<inglise> This burden shall not be disproportionate when it is sufficiently remedied by measures existing within the framework of the disability policy of the Member State concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asjaomase liikmesriigi invaliidsuspoliitika raames kohaldatavad meetmed on piisavalt heastavad, ei ole see koormus ebaproportsionaalselt suur. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Justification of differences of treatment on grounds of age </inglise>
<eesti> Vanuse alusel erineva kohtlemise &otilde;igustatus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding Article 2(2), Member States may provide that differences of treatment on grounds of age shall not constitute discrimination, if, within the context of national law, they are objectively and reasonably justified by a legitimate aim, including legitimate employment policy, labour market and vocational training objectives, and if the means of achieving that aim are appropriate and necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata artikli 2 l&otilde;ikest 2 v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid ette n&auml;ha, et erinevat kohtlemist vanuse alusel ei peeta diskrimineerimiseks, kui sellel on siseriikliku &otilde;igusega objektiivselt ja m&otilde;istlikult p&otilde;hjendatud, t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivepoliitikat, t&ouml;&ouml;turgu ja kutse&otilde;pet h&otilde;lmav &otilde;igustatud eesm&auml;rk ning kui selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamise vahendid on asjakohased ja vajalikud. </eesti>
<inglise> Such differences of treatment may include, among others: </inglise>
<eesti> Selline erinev kohtlemine v&otilde;ib muu hulgas seisneda j&auml;rgmises: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the setting of special conditions on access to employment and vocational training, employment and occupation, including dismissal and remuneration conditions, for young people, older workers and persons with caring responsibilities in order to promote their vocational integration or ensure their protection; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&ouml;&ouml;le ja kutse&otilde;ppele p&auml;&auml;semise, t&ouml;&ouml; saamise ja kutsealale p&auml;&auml;semise ning t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamise ja palga eritingimuste kehtestamine noortele, vanematele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ja hooldamiskohustusi t&auml;itvatele isikutele, et edendada nende kutsealast integreerimist v&otilde;i tagada nende kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the fixing of minimum conditions of age, professional experience or seniority in service for access to employment or to certain advantages linked to employment; </inglise>
<eesti> b) vanuse, t&ouml;&ouml;kogemuse v&otilde;i teenistusalase vanemusega seotud t&ouml;&ouml;le p&auml;&auml;semise v&otilde;i teatavate t&ouml;&ouml;soodustuste miinimumtingimuste kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the fixing of a maximum age for recruitment which is based on the training requirements of the post in question or the need for a reasonable period of employment before retirement. </inglise>
<eesti> c) t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmise vanuse &uuml;lempiiri kehtestamine k&otilde;nealuse ametikoha koolitusn&otilde;uete alusel v&otilde;i selleks, et pensionile j&auml;&auml;misele eelneks m&otilde;istlik t&ouml;&ouml;staa&zcaron;. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding Article 2(2), Member States may provide that the fixing for occupational social security schemes of ages for admission or entitlement to retirement or invalidity benefits, including the fixing under those schemes of different ages for employees or groups or categories of employees, and the use, in the context of such schemes, of age criteria in actuarial calculations, does not constitute discrimination on the grounds of age, provided this does not result in discrimination on the grounds of sex. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata artikli 2 l&otilde;ikest 2 v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid ette n&auml;ha, et vanusepiiride kehtestamist kutsealaste sotsiaalkindlustuskavade pensioni- v&otilde;i invaliidsush&uuml;vitiste saamiseks, sealhulgas t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate r&uuml;hmadele v&otilde;i kategooriatele eri vanusepiiride kehtestamist nende kavade raames, ning vanusekategooriate kasutamist kindlustusstatistikas ei peeta vanuseliseks diskrimineerimiseks, kui sellest ei tulene soolist diskrimineerimist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Positive action </inglise>
<eesti> Positiivne toimimisviis </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> With a view to ensuring full equality in practice, the principle of equal treatment shall not prevent any Member State from maintaining or adopting specific measures to prevent or compensate for disadvantages linked to any of the grounds referred to in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Silmas pidades t&auml;ieliku v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse tegelikku tagamist, ei takista v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;te &uuml;htki liikmesriiki s&auml;ilitamast v&otilde;i kehtestamast erimeetmeid &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millise artiklis 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjusega seotud halvemuse &auml;rahoidmiseks v&otilde;i heastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> With regard to disabled persons, the principle of equal treatment shall be without prejudice to the right of Member States to maintain or adopt provisions on the protection of health and safety at work or to measures aimed at creating or maintaining provisions or facilities for safeguarding or promoting their integration into the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti> Puuetega inimeste osas ei piira v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;te liikmesriikide &otilde;igust s&auml;ilitada v&otilde;i vastu v&otilde;tta t&ouml;&ouml;l tervisekaitset ja ohutust k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid v&otilde;i kohaldada meetmeid, mille eesm&auml;rk on luua v&otilde;i s&auml;ilitada norme v&otilde;i soodustusi, mis kaitsevad v&otilde;i edendavad puuetega inimeste t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonda integreerimist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Minimum requirements </inglise>
<eesti> Miinimumn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may introduce or maintain provisions which are more favourable to the protection of the principle of equal treatment than those laid down in this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad kehtestada v&otilde;i s&auml;ilitada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tetest soodsamad v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet kaitsvad s&auml;tted. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The implementation of this Directive shall under no circumstances constitute grounds for a reduction in the level of protection against discrimination already afforded by Member States in the fields covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamine ei &otilde;igusta mingil juhul selle diskrimineerimisvastase kaitstuse taseme alandamist, mis k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas oli liikmesriikides juba varem olemas. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER II </inglise>
<eesti> II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise> REMEDIES AND ENFORCEMENT </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;IGUSKAITSEVAHENDID JA OTSUSTE T&Auml;ITMINE </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> Defence of rights </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;iguste kaitse </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that judicial and/or administrative procedures, including where they deem it appropriate conciliation procedures, for the enforcement of obligations under this Directive are available to all persons who consider themselves wronged by failure to apply the principle of equal treatment to them, even after the relationship in which the discrimination is alleged to have occurred has ended. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et iga&uuml;hel, kes leiab, et teda on v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte eiramise t&otilde;ttu koheldud &otilde;igusvastaselt, oleks v&otilde;imalik kasutada k&auml;esolevast direktiivist tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks etten&auml;htud haldus- v&otilde;i kohtumenetlust, kaasa arvatud lepitusmenetlust, isegi juhul, kui see t&ouml;&ouml;suhe, millega v&auml;idetav diskrimineerimine kaasnes, on l&otilde;ppenud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that associations, organisations or other legal entities which have, in accordance with the criteria laid down by their national law, a legitimate interest in ensuring that the provisions of this Directive are complied with, may engage, either on behalf or in support of the complainant, with his or her approval, in any judicial and/or administrative procedure provided for the enforcement of obligations under this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et &uuml;hingud, organisatsioonid v&otilde;i juriidilised isikud, kellel koosk&otilde;las siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud kriteeriumidega on &otilde;igustatud huvi tagada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tete j&auml;rgimine, v&otilde;iksid kaebuse esitaja n&otilde;usolekul esineda tema nimel v&otilde;i toetuseks kohtu- ja/v&otilde;i haldusmenetluses, mis toimub k&auml;esolevast direktiivist tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraphs 1 and 2 are without prejudice to national rules relating to time limits for bringing actions as regards the principle of equality of treatment. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;iked 1 ja 2 ei piira selliste siseriiklike eeskirjade kohaldamist, millega kehtestatakse v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte k&uuml;simuses menetluse algatamise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Burden of proof </inglise>
<eesti> T&otilde;endamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take such measures as are necessary, in accordance with their national judicial systems, to ensure that, when persons who consider themselves wronged because the principle of equal treatment has not been applied to them establish, before a court or other competent authority, facts from which it may be presumed that there has been direct or indirect discrimination, it shall be for the respondent to prove that there has been no breach of the principle of equal treatment. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad koosk&otilde;las oma siseriikliku kohtus&uuml;steemiga vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et kui isik, kes leiab, et ta on v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaldamata j&auml;tmise t&otilde;ttu kannatanud, esitab kohtule v&otilde;i muule p&auml;devale asutusele asjaolud, mille p&otilde;hjal v&otilde;ib eeldada, et on toimunud otsene v&otilde;i kaudne diskrimineerimine, peab kostja t&otilde;endama, et v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet ei ole rikutud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraph 1 shall not prevent Member States from introducing rules of evidence which are more favourable to plaintiffs. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ige 1 ei takista liikmesriikidel kehtestamast hagejale soodsamaid t&otilde;endamisreegleid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraph 1 shall not apply to criminal procedures. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;iget 1 ei kohaldata kriminaalmenetluse suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraphs 1, 2 and 3 shall also apply to any legal proceedings commenced in accordance with Article 9(2). </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikeid 1, 2 ja 3 kohaldatakse ka kohtumenetluste suhtes, mida on alustatud vastavalt artikli 9 l&otilde;ikele 2. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States need not apply paragraph 1 to proceedings in which it is for the court or competent body to investigate the facts of the case. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid ei pea kohaldama l&otilde;iget 1 menetluste suhtes, mille korral juhtumi asjaolude uurimine on kohtu v&otilde;i p&auml;deva asutuse &uuml;lesanne. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> Victimisation </inglise>
<eesti> Ohvristamine </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall introduce into their national legal systems such measures as are necessary to protect employees against dismissal or other adverse treatment by the employer as a reaction to a complaint within the undertaking or to any legal proceedings aimed at enforcing compliance with the principle of equal treatment. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid rakendavad oma siseriiklikus &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemis meetmed, mis on vajalikud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kaitsmiseks t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamise v&otilde;i muu pahatahtliku kohtlemise eest, kui see on t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutegevus ettev&otilde;ttesisesele kaebusele v&otilde;i kohtumenetlusele, mille eesm&auml;rk on tagada v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgimine. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> Dissemination of information </inglise>
<eesti> Teabelevi </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take care that the provisions adopted pursuant to this Directive, together with the relevant provisions already in force in this field, are brought to the attention of the persons concerned by all appropriate means, for example at the workplace, throughout their territory. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel vastuv&otilde;etud s&auml;tted ja selles valdkonnas juba kehtivad s&auml;tted tehakse liikmesriikide territooriumil asjaomastele isikutele sobival viisil, n&auml;iteks t&ouml;&ouml;kohal, teatavaks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> Social dialogue </inglise>
<eesti> Sotsiaalne dialoog </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall, in accordance with their national traditions and practice, take adequate measures to promote dialogue between the social partners with a view to fostering equal treatment, including through the monitoring of workplace practices, collective agreements, codes of conduct and through research or exchange of experiences and good practices. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vastavalt siseriiklikele traditsioonidele ja tavadele asjakohaseid meetmeid, et edendada t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel dialoogi, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on toetada v&otilde;rdset kohtlemist, kontrollides muu hulgas olukorda t&ouml;&ouml;kohas, koostades kollektiivlepinguid ja tegevusjuhendeid ning uurides ja vahetades kogemusi ja h&auml;id tavasid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where consistent with their national traditions and practice, Member States shall encourage the social partners, without prejudice to their autonomy, to conclude at the appropriate level agreements laying down anti-discrimination rules in the fields referred to in Article 3 which fall within the scope of collective bargaining. </inglise>
<eesti> Piiramata t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte autonoomiat ning koosk&otilde;las siseriiklike traditsioonide ja tavadega, &auml;rgitavad liikmesriigid t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooli s&otilde;lmima n&otilde;uetekohasel tasemel kokkuleppeid, milles s&auml;testatakse diskrimineerimisvastased eeskirjad artiklis 3 nimetatud valdkondades, mis kuuluvad kollektiivl&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste reguleerimisalasse. </eesti>
<inglise> These agreements shall respect the minimum requirements laid down by this Directive and by the relevant national implementing measures. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealused kokkulepped peavad vastama k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga kehtestatud miinimumn&otilde;uetele ja vastavatele siseriiklikele rakendusmeetmetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> Dialogue with non-governmental organisations </inglise>
<eesti> Dialoog valitsusv&auml;liste organisatsioonidega </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall encourage dialogue with appropriate non-governmental organisations which have, in accordance with their national law and practice, a legitimate interest in contributing to the fight against discrimination on any of the grounds referred to in Article 1 with a view to promoting the principle of equal treatment. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid toetavad dialoogi asjaomaste valitsusv&auml;liste organisatsioonidega, kellel on koosk&otilde;las siseriikliku &otilde;iguse v&otilde;i tavaga &otilde;igustatud huvi kaasa aidata v&otilde;itlusele &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millise artiklis 1 nimetatud p&otilde;hjusest tingitud diskrimineerimise vastu, et edendada v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgmist. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER III </inglise>
<eesti> III PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> PARTICULAR PROVISIONS </inglise>
<eesti> ERIS&Auml;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> Northern Ireland </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hja-Iirimaa </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to tackle the under-representation of one of the major religious communities in the police service of Northern Ireland, differences in treatment regarding recruitment into that service, including its support staff, shall not constitute discrimination insofar as those differences in treatment are expressly authorised by national legislation. </inglise>
<eesti> Et arvesse v&otilde;tta &uuml;he suurema usukogukonna alaesindatust P&otilde;hja-Iirimaa politseiteenistuses, ei peeta P&otilde;hja-Iirimaa politsei- v&otilde;i abipersonali t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmisel ilmnevat erinevat kohtlemist diskrimineerimiseks, kui see on lubatud siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to maintain a balance of opportunity in employment for teachers in Northern Ireland while furthering the reconciliation of historical divisions between the major religious communities there, the provisions on religion or belief in this Directive shall not apply to the recruitment of teachers in schools in Northern Ireland in so far as this is expressly authorised by national legislation. </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;petajate v&otilde;rdsete t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imaluste s&auml;ilitamiseks P&otilde;hja-Iirimaal ja selleks, et edendada sealsete suuremate usukogukondade vaheliste ajalooliste erimeelsuste lahendamist, ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva direktiivi usutunnistust v&otilde;i veendumusi k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid P&otilde;hja-Iirimaal &otilde;petajate t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmise suhtes, kui see on lubatud siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER IV </inglise>
<eesti> IV PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> FINAL PROVISIONS </inglise>
<eesti> L&Otilde;PPS&Auml;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> Compliance </inglise>
<eesti> J&auml;rgimine </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take the necessary measures to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vajalikud meetmed, et tagada: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) any laws, regulations and administrative provisions contrary to the principle of equal treatment are abolished; </inglise>
<eesti> a) k&otilde;ikide v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttega vastuolus olevate &otilde;igusnormide t&uuml;histamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) any provisions contrary to the principle of equal treatment which are included in contracts or collective agreements, internal rules of undertakings or rules governing the independent occupations and professions and workers' and employers' organisations are, or may be, declared null and void or are amended. </inglise>
<eesti> b) lepingutes v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingutes, ettev&otilde;tete sisekorraeeskirjades v&otilde;i vabakutseliste ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate organisatsioonide tegevust reguleerivates eeskirjades sisalduvate v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttega vastuolus olevate s&auml;tete kehtetuks tunnistamine v&otilde;i luba need kehtetuks tunnistada v&otilde;i neid muuta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 17 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 17 </eesti>
<inglise> Sanctions </inglise>
<eesti> Sanktsioonid </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall lay down the rules on sanctions applicable to infringements of the national provisions adopted pursuant to this Directive and shall take all measures necessary to ensure that they are applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kehtestavad eeskirjad sanktsioonide kohta, mida rakendatakse vastavalt k&auml;esolevale direktiivile vastuv&otilde;etud siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide rikkumise korral, ning v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et tagada nende kohaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise> The sanctions, which may comprise the payment of compensation to the victim, must be effective, proportionate and dissuasive. </inglise>
<eesti> Sanktsioonid, milleks v&otilde;ib olla ohvrile kahju h&uuml;vitamine, peavad olema t&otilde;husad, proportsionaalsed ja hoiatavad. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall notify those provisions to the Commission by 2 December 2003 at the latest and shall notify it without delay of any subsequent amendment affecting them. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad neist s&auml;tetest komisjonile hiljemalt 2. detsembriks 2003 ja annavad viivitamata teada nende edaspidistest muudatustest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 18 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 18 </eesti>
<inglise> Implementation </inglise>
<eesti> Rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive by 2 December 2003 at the latest or may entrust the social partners, at their joint request, with the implementation of this Directive as regards provisions concerning collective agreements. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid vastu hiljemalt 2. detsembriks 2003 v&otilde;i v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamise selle kollektiivlepinguid k&auml;sitlevas osas usaldada t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooltele nende &uuml;hise taotluse p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> In such cases, Member States shall ensure that, no later than 2 December 2003, the social partners introduce the necessary measures by agreement, the Member States concerned being required to take any necessary measures to enable them at any time to be in a position to guarantee the results imposed by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul tagab liikmesriik, et hiljemalt 2. detsembriks 2003 on t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled kokkuleppel kehtestanud vajalikud meetmed, kusjuures asjaomased liikmesriigid peavad v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, mis v&otilde;imaldavad neil igal ajal tagada k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga n&otilde;utud tulemused. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to take account of particular conditions, Member States may, if necessary, have an additional period of 3 years from 2 December 2003, that is to say a total of 6 years, to implement the provisions of this Directive on age and disability discrimination. </inglise>
<eesti> Et arvesse v&otilde;tta eritingimusi, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid p&auml;rast 2. detsembrit 2003 vajaduse korral saada kolmeaastase lisaaja, seega kokku kuus aastat, et rakendada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vanuse ja puude alusel diskrimineerimist k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> In that event they shall inform the Commission forthwith. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul teatavad nad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Any Member State which chooses to use this additional period shall report annually to the Commission on the steps it is taking to tackle age and disability discrimination and on the progress it is making towards implementation. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik, kes seda lisaaega kasutab, esitab igal aastal komisjonile aruande vanuse ja puude alusel diskrimineerimise vastu v&otilde;itlemiseks v&otilde;etavate meetmete ja k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamise edusammude kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall report annually to the Council. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab igal aastal aruande n&otilde;ukogule. </eesti>
<inglise> When Member States adopt these measures, they shall contain a reference to this Directive or be accompanied by such reference on the occasion of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid need meetmed vastu v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse meetmetesse v&otilde;i nende meetmete ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The methods of making such reference shall be laid down by Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellise viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 19 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 19 </eesti>
<inglise> Report </inglise>
<eesti> Aruanne </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall communicate to the Commission, by 2 December 2005 at the latest and every five years thereafter, all the information necessary for the Commission to draw up a report to the European Parliament and the Council on the application of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad hiljemalt 2. detsembriks 2005 ja seej&auml;rel iga viie aasta tagant komisjonile kogu vajaliku teabe, et komisjon saaks Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule koostada aruande k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission's report shall take into account, as appropriate, the viewpoints of the social partners and relevant non-governmental organisations. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni aruandes v&otilde;etakse vajaduse korral arvesse t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte ja asjaomaste valitsusv&auml;liste organisatsioonide seisukohti. </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with the principle of gender mainstreaming, this report shall, inter alia, provide an assessment of the impact of the measures taken on women and men. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt soolise v&otilde;rd&otilde;iguslikkuse igas eluvaldkonnas rakendamise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele (mainstreaming) peab selles aruandes muu hulgas sisalduma hinnang, kuidas v&otilde;etud meetmed on m&otilde;junud naistele ja meestele. </eesti>
<inglise> In the light of the information received, this report shall include, if necessary, proposals to revise and update this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt saadud andmetele v&otilde;ib see aruanne vajaduse korral sisaldada ettepanekuid k&auml;esolev direktiiv l&auml;bi vaadata ja ajakohastada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 20 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 20 </eesti>
<inglise> Entry into force </inglise>
<eesti> J&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiiv j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
 